    "While still professor in Munich, Burger became a soldier in World War I. During the breaks in the war he wrote about culture and philosophy, including a theoretical essay, the <em>Einf\u00fchrung in die moderne Kunst</em>.": [],
    "He was killed at age 39 in the bloody battle at Verdun.": [],
    "Brinckmann assumed Burger's work as editor of the <em>Handbuch</em> and the publication of the <em>Einf\u00fchrung</em>.": [
